webpackJsonp([155],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/articles-python-python-slicestartstopstep.json":function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p><code>slice(start:stop[:step])</code> is an object usually containing a portion of a sequence. A slice is created using the subscript notation, [] with colons between numbers when several are given, such as in variable_name[1:3:5].</p>\n<h2>Arguments</h2>\n<p>This function can be used to slice tuples, arrays and lists.</p>\n<p>The value of the <code>start</code> parameter (or None if not provided)</p>\n<p>The value of the <code>stop</code> parameter (or last index of sequence)</p>\n<p>The value of the <code>step</code> parameter (or None if not provided). It cannot be 0.</p>\n<p>All three must be of integer type.</p>\n<h2>Return</h2>\n<p>If only <code>stop</code> is provided, it generates portion of sequence from index <code>0</code> till <code>stop</code>.</p>\n<p>If only <code>start</code> is provided, it generates portion of sequence after index <code>start</code> till last element.</p>\n<p>If both <code>start</code> and <code>stop</code> are provided, it generates portion of sequence after index <code>start</code> till <code>stop</code>.</p>\n<p>If all three <code>start</code>, <code>stop</code> and <code>step</code> are provided, it generates portion of sequence after index <code>start</code> till <code>stop</code> with increment of index <code>step</code>.</p>\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<pre><code>a = [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\nprint(a[:5])    # prints [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\nprint(a[2:])    # prints [3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\nprint(a[2:5])    # prints [3, 4, 5]\nprint(a[2:7:2])    # prints [3, 5, 7]\n</code></pre>\n<p><img src="//forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/rocket.png?v=2" alt=":rocket:" title=":rocket:"> <a href="https://repl.it/CT5h">Run Code</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#slice">Official Documentation</a></p>',frontmatter:{title:"Python Slicestartstopstep",parent:"/home/stuart/guides/src/pages/articles/python/python-slicestartstopstep/index.md absPath of file"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/articles/python/python-slicestartstopstep/"}}}});
